00:52:38.590 --> 00:52:44.680
Would you say that Apple's experience with
Foxconn in China is a result of their corporate

00:52:44.680 --> 00:52:49.960
strategies and focus and the like or is that
sort of anomalous having to do with labor

00:52:49.960 --> 00:52:55.010
conditions in general in China, does it come
from Apple or is Apple just sort of a semi-willing

00:52:55.010 --> 00:52:56.010
participant.

00:52:56.010 --> 00:53:02.630
&gt;&gt;Adam Lashinsky: So the question is, is Apple's
experience at Foxconn in China, essentially

00:53:02.630 --> 00:53:08.220
I'll recraft your question, is it exceptional,
is it different from the industry?

00:53:08.220 --> 00:53:13.540
And I have not gone deep on this topic so
my superficial understanding first of all

00:53:13.540 --> 00:53:21.940
is that no their experiences in China are
similar to everybody else's experiences.

00:53:21.940 --> 00:53:28.040
And if anything, and I am neither excusing
them nor criticizing them for what goes on

00:53:28.040 --> 00:53:35.830
in China, but am observing that Apple culturally
is unused to being the top dog; they're unused

00:53:35.830 --> 00:53:41.120
to the scrutiny of being number one; they
identify with being the underdog, so I think

00:53:41.120 --> 00:53:44.090
they were shocked that they were being singled
out.

00:53:44.090 --> 00:53:48.110
We'll find out if they're better or worse
than everybody else but I think if you look

00:53:48.110 --> 00:53:53.310
at the New York Times' article that has put
this back on the agenda or has elevated this

00:53:53.310 --> 00:53:59.360
on the agenda, the Times went to great length
to suggest that the article that it did on

00:53:59.360 --> 00:54:04.780
the situation at Foxconn could have been written
about any of the big consumer electronics

00:54:04.780 --> 00:54:10.650
manufacturers who used contract manufacturers
in China, which is all of them.

00:54:10.650 --> 00:54:19.260
And you saw today that Apple has hired a third
party auditor to audit themselves again and

00:54:19.260 --> 00:54:20.401
so we'll see how that goes.

